File: The Gauteng provincial government has confirmed that all employees at the Anglo Gold Ashanti's Mponeng mine have been admitted to an isolation facility. JOHANNESBURG - At least 75 workers at Anglo Gold Ashanti's Mponeng Mine in Gauteng have tested positive for COVID-19.
The Gauteng provincial government has confirmed that all employees have been admitted to an isolation facility. READ: Mines brace for potential COVID-19 infections A team has been sent to trace all known contacts. The management of the mine says all underground miners have been tested and 104 results are still outstanding. Underground production will remain closed until further notice. Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.